onyl </h2> <p><strong>Beyond Skin</strong><br />Cruelty-free shoes that use alternatives to leather</p> <p><strong>Jocelyn Whipple </strong><br />Reusing a hand knitted Rowan jumper by her grandmother for over 24 years </p> <p><strong>The Ecoture™ Project</strong><br />Deborah Milner and Karen Spurgin designed the Rousseau dress, which is made with leftover silk and influenced by the Yawanawa people of the Amazon</p> <p><strong>K2TOG, Katie Jones </strong><br />Created an embroidered peplum jumper using yarn from upcycled jumper sources</p> <p><strong>Antithesis </strong><br />A fashion label based on creating versatile, enduring wardrobe essentials with changeable accessories</p> <h2>The Great Energy Race in association with B&amp;Q</h2> <p><strong>Robin Cathcart </strong>- Environmental scientist living in Edinburgh</p> <p><strong>Jen Gale</strong> - veterinarian and blogger from Wiltshire</p> <p><strong>Hannah Goddard</strong> - Renovating her home in Worcestershire</p> <p><strong>Kate Harrison </strong>- Community energy champion from Ashton Hayes</p> <p><strong>Peter Hawkins</strong> - Gardener living in Hertfordshire</p> <p><strong>Steve Huckle</strong> - Lives in a Victorian home in Southwick</p> <p><strong>David Kemp</strong> - family from Sheffield</p> <p><strong>James Murnaghan</strong> - Sustainability manager from Coventry</p> <p><strong>Tom Yearley </strong>- University Energy Officer living in Reading</p> <h2>Best in business</h2> <p><strong>LUSH </strong><br />A company that makes and retails fresh handmade beauty products using natural ingredients</p> <p><strong>Ento </strong><br />A startup focused on encouraging the eating of insects as a sustainable and alternative source of protein in Western diets</p> <p><strong>We Deliver Local </strong><br />Offers an easy way for local businesses to integrate their delivery services and offers people a convenient way to shop locally and support small businesses</p> <h2>Arts and culture</h2> <p><strong>Mat Fraser</strong><br />Cabinet of Curiosities: How Disabilities was kept in a box - a performance based piece to highlight how disabled people are portrayed in museums</p> <p><strong>West Yorkshire Playhouse&apos;s production of Refugee Boy </strong><br />A theatre production to provoke thought on the current issues surrounding refugees and asylum seekers</p> <p><strong>Amar Kanwar: The Sovereign Forest + Other Stories </strong><br />A moving exhibition, at Yorkshire Sculpture Park, exploring the impact of mining and other commercial activities on the landscape and communities of Odisha, India</p> <h2><strong> The reader-voted shortlists are:</strong></h2> <h2>Campaigner of the year</h2> <p><strong>Brian May CBE </strong><br />An animal rights campaigner and founder of Save-Me and Team Badger</p> <p><strong>Carry Somers </strong><br />The founder of Fashion Revolution encourages fashion lovers to connect with the people who make the clothes, and give a voice to everyone in the supply chain</p> <p><strong>Vanessa Vine </strong><br />Founder of BIFF! Britain &amp; Ireland Frack Free and Frack Free Sussex - campaigning tirelessly to raise awareness of the dangers of unconventional fossil fuel exploitation.</p> <p><strong>Anne Power </strong><br />A supporter of anti-fracking protests and protesters</p> <p><strong>Nicola Peel </strong><br />An environmentalist and film maker dedicated to practical solutions around the world</p> <h2>Retailer of the year</h2> <p><strong>Growing Communities </strong><br />A Hackney social enterprise running an organic local farmers market</p> <p><strong>Babi Pur </strong><br />A family-run online retailer based in Snowdonia that offers ethical baby and early years products</p> <p><strong>Riverford </strong><br />A vegbox company founded by Guy Watson, which supports small scale family farms and minimises its own carbon footprint</p> <p><strong>RoCo </strong><br />An Irish eco-organic salon that makes its own organic products and has an in-salon recycling points</p> <p><strong>hiSbe </strong><br />A social enterprise in Brighton to make good food more affordable</p> <h2>Local hero </h2> <p><strong>Anne Power </strong><br />A supporter of anti-fracking protests and protesters</p> <p><strong>Barton Moss Community Protection Camp </strong><br />A group dedicated to resisting extreme energy extraction</p> <p><strong>Georgina Downs </strong><br />A campaigner against pesticides in communities, who has secured changes to policy in the UK, and EU laws</p> <p><strong>John Herbert</strong><br />Founder of Cre8 Lifestyle Centre, an arts and community hub in Hackney</p> <p><strong>Pushpanath Krishnamurthy </strong><br />A social justice and climate campaigner</p>","wordcount":"817","commentable":"false","creationDate":"2014-05-13T15:15:31Z","internalComposerCode":"56998155e4b0d16f7ae70faa","internalOctopusCode":"2091967","internalPageCode":"2091967","isPremoderated":"false","lastModified":"2014-05-23T11:14:49Z","newspaperEditionDate":"2014-05-13T00:00:00Z","productionOffice":"UK","publication":"theguardian.com","shortUrl":"https://gu.com/p/3p7h7","shouldHideAdverts":"false","showInRelatedContent":"true","legallySensitive":"false","lang":"en","internalRevision":"1","internalShortId":"/p/3p7h7"},"apiUrl":"https://content.guardianapis.com/observer-ethical-awards/shortlist-2014","webUrl":"https://www.theguardian.com/observer-ethical-awards/shortlist-2014","webTitle":"Observer Ethical Awards 2014 shortlist","webPublicationDate":"2014-05-15T07:01:00Z","sectionName":"Observer Ethical Awards","sectionId":"observer-ethical-awards","type":"article","id":"observer-ethical-awards/shortlist-2014","rights":{"syndicatable":"true"},"section":{"id":"observer-ethical-awards","webTitle":"Observer Ethical Awards","webUrl":"https://www.theguardian.com/observer-ethical-awards","apiUrl":"https://content.guardianapis.com/observer-ethical-awards","editions":[{"id":"observer-ethical-awards","webTitle":"Observer Ethical Awards","webUrl":"https